  "body": "[comment]: # (Please replace ... with your information. Remove < and >)\r\n\r\n### User Story\r\n\r\nAs a user, I want to be made aware when the app is not usable, so I can more quickly diagnose what is happening.\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Feature or Bug? i.e Type: Bug)\r\n*Type*: Feature\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Describe the feature you would like, or briefly summarise the bug and what you did, what you expected to happen, and what actually happens. Sections below)\r\n*Summary*: Currently if `StartNode` fails on the go side (e.g. log file cannot be created at https://github.com/status-im/status-go/blob/develop/lib/library.go#L45), then the node is not started but the user is not informed that the app is not functional.\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n[comment]: # (Describe what you expected to happen.)\r\nAn alert is shown to the user saying that the app could not start correctly.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n[comment]: # (Describe what actually happened.)\r\nThe node is not started and all the functionality is broken (e.g. cannot recover an account, nothing happens)\r\n\n\n<blockquote><img src=\"https://avatars3.githubusercontent.com/u/11767950?s=400&v=4\" width=\"48\" align=\"right\"><div><img src=\"https://assets-cdn.github.com/favicon.ico\" height=\"14\"> GitHub</div><div><strong><a href=\"https://github.com/status-im/status-go\">status-im/status-go</a></strong></div><div>status-go - The Status module that consumes go-ethereum</div></blockquote>",
